records.addlTxt:
Order Joining Matters for Trial
Based upon the stipulation of the parties these matters are joined for trial.

There is not agreement and defense counsel asks that these matters be set for trial.   Defendant is rejecting the State's offer.   
Counsel agree that both cases should be joined for trial and stipulate to that agreement.   State will file an Amended Information.   
Jury trial is set for 04-25-22 and 04-26-22 at 8:30 a.m.    Pretrial conference is set for 03-28-22 at 1:15 p.m.

2:21 pm - Prosecuting attorney Angelina R Scarpelli appeared in court for the State of Wisconsin, Defendant Joseph Lee Gunzel appeared in court.  Attorney Steve Richards represents the defendant on another matter and defendant thought he was going to be here today.  Initial appearance is reset to 03-28-22 at 1:30 p.m. to allow defendant to contact Atty. Richards.
Adjourned initial appearance on March 28, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

BAIL HEARING - 
Defendant in custody and appearing by video from the Manitowoc County Jail.  The State informs the Court that the defendant will be charged with the crime of felony bail jumping and domestic abuse injunction violation.  The matter is continued for initial appearance on 03-21-22 at 1:30 pm.  Bail is set at $1,000.00 recognizance bond with the conditions that he report to the Manitowoc City Police Department for fingerprints, photographs and identifying information within 48 hours or, if incarcerated, within 72 hours of release.  Bail furnished and defendant is released from custody.
